Sum-up

Introduction¶

In the following sections we will test several algorithms of weigths allocation of strategies with different parameters. The weights allocation is called a Blend, and we define a blend as the following:

Blend=∑i=1Mwi×SiBlend=∑i=1Mwi×Si
Such that: ∑i=1M|wi|=1Such that: ∑i=1M|wi|=1

To determine this weights we backtest five algorithms:

  • 'Equaly Weighted' Blend is an equaly weighted combination (benchmark).
  • 'Inverse Variance Porfolio' (IVP) Blend.
  • 'Minimum Variance Portfolio' (MVP) Blend, classical allocation following the Markowitz theory.
  • 'Hierchical Risk Parity' (HRP) Blend is a clustering method of the correlation matrix developped by Marcos Lopez de Prado
  • 'Maximum Diversified Portfolio' Blend developped by TOBAM.

Rolling periods¶

We select 3 months of training period N=63 and 1 month of prediction period S=21.

Same weight is allowed for each strategy.

wi=1Nwi=1N

IV - HRP allocation¶

Hierachical Risk Parity method doesn't need inverse matrix correlation, this mean it's possible to create a portofolio also based on singular covariance matrix. This method is done in three steps:

  • Tree clustering;
  • Quasi-diagonalization;
  • Recursive bisection.

For more details refer to the research paper of Marcos Lopez de Prado.
